          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "1/v dependence on the neutron energy was assumed with",
                "a Westcott factor of 1.",
                "Only samples 6b and 7b are considered for the cross",
                "section calculation and the mean 14C/13C ratio of",
                " (1.159 +- 0.021)x10**12 is taken from the AMS",
                "measurements. This is then divided by the product of",
                "the irradiation time (34260 s) and the measured flux",
                "for experiment two ((2.20 +- 0.09)x10**10 n/cm2/s) to",
                "give a final 14C production cross section of",
                "1.538 +- 0.069mb. This value is then reduced by",
                " (0.93 +- 0.39)% to account for the estimated",
                "14C production from 14N(n,p) to give the final result.",
                "           Sample        14C/13C(x10**-12)",
                "              13C/1a     1.173 +- 0.021",
                "              13C/2a     1.172 +- 0.013",
                "              13C/3a     1.199 +- 0.022",
                "              13C/4a     0.622 +- 0.010",
                "              13C/5a    0.0011 +- 0.0003",
                "              13C/6b     1.154 +- 0.025",
                "              13C/7b     1.166 +- 0.014",
                "              13C/8b    0.0013 +- 0.0007",
                "              13C/9b    0.0017 +- 0.0008",
                "             natC/10b     2.41 +- 0.14",
                "             natC/11b     1.86 +- 0.15",
                "             natC/12b         5150",
                "             IAEA C3     139.9 +- 1.4",
                "             IAEA C6     164.5 +- 1.3",
                "               CTW2      135.5 +- 4.4"
              ]
            }
